  {
    "client_msg_id": "c43577ce-13b7-432a-b106-dce9a9045cf6",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "I think most of us here feel similarly. This is a good place to exchange ideas, feedback, and resources. Most of us have found inspiration by Alan Kay and/or Bret Victor, which is a great place to start if you are interested in the idea of getting out of the programming tar-pit you describe. Find Alan Kay on YouTube (e.g. \"computer revolution hasn't happened yet\" or \"programming and scaling\"), and Bret Victor at <http://worrydream.com|worrydream.com>. There's also since good write-ups at <http://vpri.org|vpri.org>.\n\nAlso, checkout the Future of Coding podcasts",
    "user": "UAVCC2X70",
    "ts": "1556332843.008300",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_profile": {
